Write a python program that initially stores user-provided numbers in an array, displays them, and then inserts a given number at a specified location while also deleting a number from a specified location
Note:
Refer to the displayed test cases for better understanding.
The driver function is already given in the editor.

arr = [int(x) for x in input("Enter numbers separated by spaces: ").split()]
print("Array:", arr)
insert_num = int(input("Enter the number to insert: "))
insert_index = int(input("Enter the index to insert at: "))
arr.insert(insert_index, insert_num)
print("Array after insertion:", arr)
delete_index = int(input("Enter the index to delete: "))
del arr[delete_index]
print("Array after deletion:", arr)
